title: For Trade:  Akdal MKA 1919
postcontent:
The Akdal MKA 1919 is a gas operated, semi-automatic shotgun manufactured in Turkey by Ucyildiz Arms*. The MKA 1919 not only resembles the M16 rifle but the control and function are similar. The MKA 1919 is unlike any other 12 gauge shotgun in the U.S. as it is very light, ergonomic, and magazine fed. The MKA 1919 semi-automatic shotgun uses a conventional gas-operated action which is located around the support tube that runs below the barrel. The return spring is also located around the same support tube which is concealed by an enlarged polymer handguard. The MKA 1919 barrel can be very easily removed from the upper receiver. The upper receiver is manufactured from an aluminum alloy while the lower receiver, pistol grip, and stock are manufactured as one piece from impact resistant polymer. The MKA 1919 comes with four 5-round metal detachable magazines and 3 internal chokes. The magazine release button mimics the M16 rifle location. The manual safety also duplicates the M16 style being located on the left side of the receiver above the pistol grip. The top of the receiver has a carrying handle and integral picatinny rail for mounting rear sights, or any optical accessories. The MKA 1919 12 gauge shotgun is appropriate for all levels of hunting and sporting enthusiasts.

title: For Sale:  Custom Monte Carlo Remington 1100 (2 ¾” action).
postcontent:
Custom Monte Carlo Remington 1100 (2 ¾” action).

The price has been lowered $200 due to a blemish and also marks from hunting. THE BLEMISH: At one time the gun had a ghost ring gun sight. When removing it, we found scratches in the grove on top of the receiver. To remove the blemish, about two inches of the grove was ground. But the grinding did not go as deep as the original flutes in the top of the receiver, so as not to compromise the strength. That two inch ground area was then cold blued, (rather than re-plating the whole receiver). See photos of cold bluing and grinding before cold blue. So this is not a “show-case” gun. It’s a fancy custom 1100 that has been used for hunting. The name WILLIAMS is stamped onto the lower right side of the receiver. WILLIAMS is the name of the gunsmith who honed and polished the slides, accurized the trigger and polished the barrel and receiver for plating. It is nickel plated with a matte stainless finish, inside and outside. The barrel is a 21’ Special Field barrel which was fitted with choke tubes by www.briley.com. Their chokes are longer and more gradually tapered than most, (and expensive). It has two chokes, Improved Cylinder and X-Full. It has a custom Monte Carlo stock which shows signs of hunting use, (dents that did not break the finish as a scratch). On the left side of the butt stock at the top of the white spacer, the recoil pad was ground thru and exposes about one inch of aluminum. It is high grade solid Missouri walnut. Original forearm is included with purchase. WILL SHIP FOR $59 TO COVER FFL HANDLING AND ACTUAL SHIPPING COSTS. Three day inspection return policy, but you pay FFL, shipping and 15% restock.
